The MIT licence above covers the source code only.

This project is an unofficial, fan-made tool. It is not affiliated with,
endorsed by, or associated with Cygames, Inc. or Bandai Namco Entertainment.
"Granblue Fantasy: Relink" and all related names, characters and content are
the property of their respective owners.

No game audio is redistributed. The tool reads and modifies only the copy of
the game already installed on the user's own machine. The one exception is
silence.wem, a 361-byte clip of digital silence used as the mute source, which
contains no speech, music or identifying metadata.

The dataset under data/ consists of factual metadata (identifiers, labels,
durations, audio formats) together with short machine-generated transcripts of
individual battle voice lines. It is published for reference and
interoperability. The underlying dialogue remains the property of its owners.
